This was achieved by pulling the northern feeder bridge 700 millimeters to the south.
This was a massive and at the same time very delicate activity.
Massive, because the viaduct is 222 meters long, weighs about 6,000 tons and had to be pulled upwards at an incline of about 3%.
Delicate, because the tolerances the team was working towards were tiny - on each side they were only a few millimeters.
