Baden-Wuerttemberg: Police determined after Rocker attack on snack
After an attack on an Ulm snack bar, the police investigate six suspects from the rocker milieu for serious breach of the peace.
Evidence and narcotics were seized during home searches, the police announced on Friday.
According to the police, about 20 masked men from a rocker-like group threw bottles and stones against the window of a snack bar in July.
Afterwards they allegedly attacked two guests and injured one of them slightly.
Then they fled.
The snack bar and the adjacent building suffered damage of 10,000 euros.
According to the investigators, there is a dispute in the Ulm rocker milieu between a Kurdish and a Turkish gang.
Thuringia: Zeiss Meditec ’ s turnover reaches billion
High demand for medical technology in Asia has boosted sales at Carl Zeiss Meditec.
In the first nine months of the financial year that began in October, Group sales increased by 6.7 percent to EUR 798.6 million, as the listed company announced on Friday in Jena.
Business in Asia grew disproportionately by 17.1 percent.
According to the interim balance sheet, earnings before interest and taxes increased from 89.5 million euros to 110.5 million euros.
The Jenaer medical technology company wants to exceed in this financial year the sales mark of one billion euro, confirmed the executive committee.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures equipment for medical practices and clinics.
The company, which belongs to the optics and electronics group Carl Zeiss (Oberkochen), employs almost 3,000 people.
